710124f-b.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 24th Street
710124f-b.text:
(1)
Eighth Avenue at S. W. corner of 24th Street.
Note Republican poster for Hoover and Curtis in 1928 pres-
idential campaign.
September 14, 1928.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.
(2)
The same, at a later date. These buildings bear Nos. 277-275 and
273 Eighth Ave. On the right of the view is seen West 24th Street, north
aide, west of Eighth Ave.
December 26, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

710125f-b.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 24th Street (West)
710125f-b.text:
Eighth Avenue, east side, north from W. 24th -treet (right),
as viewed from a point on the west side of the evenue close to
23rd Street. The large office structure shown is at N.E. corner
of W.est 2oth Street and is of recent construction.
Note the cobblestone street paverient ahd the surface car
tacks. On the completion of the Municipal Subway (Eiphth Avenue)
both of these features will disappea.
View No. 2 is taken from the e.E. corner of 24th Street and
shows a view up the east east side of the Avenue.
View 1: June 25, 1928
View 2: Mar. 21, 1938
P. L. Sperr

710126f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 24th Street (West)
710126f-a.text:
284 to 294 Eighth Avenue, east side, north of West 24th, to
25th Streets, as shown in two portions, consisting of buildings
numbered 284 to 288 (in View No. 2) and 288 to 294 (View No. 1).
The latter are at the S.E. corner of this thoroumfare and West
25th Street. Note the Eighth Avenue Mission at No. 290 and
slightly to the south of same. View No. 3 is simulwr, showing
a better perspective of the aforementioned Mission.
No. 1  June 25, 1928.
About 1910
March 21, i938.
P. L. Sperr (No's. i & 3)
Anonymous Gift (No. 2)
